📊 Newton Divided Difference Interpolation in Excel
This project implements the Newton Divided Difference method using Microsoft Excel for numerical data interpolation. The process includes constructing divided difference tables, developing Newton interpolation polynomials up to the fourth order, and estimating function values at a specific point.

Dataset used:
x	f(x)
1	1.5
3	10
5	15
7	21
9	30
The objective of this project is to understand the application of numerical methods in estimating function values from discrete data points.

Method
The Newton Interpolation Polynomial is given by:
Pn(x)=f[x1]+(x−x1)f[x2,x1]+(x−x1)(x−x2)f[x3,x2,x1]+⋯

Divided difference coefficients obtained:
Coefficient	Value
f[x₂,x₁]	4.25
f[x₃,x₂,x₁]	-0.4375
f[x₄,x₃,x₂,x₁]	0.09375
f[x₅,x₄,x₃,x₂,x₁]	-0.006510417

